('data_science','Your model gets 99% accuracy on training data but 55% on test data. What is happening and what do you do first?','The model is overfitting — try regularization, reduce complexity, or add more training data','The model is underfitting — add more features','The test data is wrong — reshuffle and retry','The accuracy metric is incorrect — switch to F1','A'),
('data_science','You load a CSV and a column has 40% NaN values. What do you do before deciding how to handle it?','Drop it immediately','Check if the missingness is random or related to other features before deciding to impute or drop','Fill all NaN with 0','Fill all NaN with the mean','B'),
('data_science','You have a dataset with 95% class 0 and 5% class 1. Your model predicts 0 for everything and gets 95% accuracy. What metric do you actually need?','Accuracy is fine for this task','Use MSE instead','Precision, recall, F1-score or AUC-ROC which account for class imbalance','Accuracy with a threshold of 0.5','C'),
('data_science','You run df.info() and see a column "price" has dtype object even though it should be numeric. What is the actual fix?','Cast it with df["price"].astype(float)','Fill NaN values first','Drop the column','The column has non-numeric characters like dollar sign or comma — clean it first then convert','D'),
('data_science','You trained a model on Jan-Nov data and tested on December. It works great but fails in production. Why?','The model has too many features','December is always an outlier month','The model needs retraining monthly','Data leakage — the model was trained on data including future info not available at prediction time','A'),
('data_science','You need to join two DataFrames on user_id and keep all rows from the left even with no right match. What do you use?','pd.merge(df1, df2, on="user_id", how="inner")','pd.merge(df1, df2, on="user_id", how="left")','pd.concat([df1, df2])','df1.join(df2, on="user_id")','B'),
('data_science','Your scikit-learn model gives different results on your machine versus your colleagues machine with same data. What did you forget?','To save the model','To normalize the data','To set random_state to a fixed value in the model and train_test_split','To print the results','C'),
('data_science','You want to find which features matter most in your Random Forest model. What do you access?','model.weights_','model.coef_','model.explain()','model.feature_importances_','D'),
('data_science','You run a SQL query and get duplicate rows in the result. What clause do you add to remove them?','DISTINCT','GROUP BY','UNIQUE','DEDUPE','A'),
('data_science','You need the top 3 salaries per department in SQL. Simple ORDER BY and LIMIT does not work across departments. What do you use?','A subquery with MAX()','ROW_NUMBER() or DENSE_RANK() partitioned by department','GROUP BY department ORDER BY salary','A self-join','B'),
('data_science','Your pandas groupby on a 10 million row DataFrame is very slow. What do you consider switching to?','A faster computer','NumPy groupby','PySpark or Dask for distributed computation','SQL in pandas','C'),
('data_science','You want to evaluate your model fairly but only have 1000 samples. Train/test split wastes data. What technique?','Use all data for training and none for testing','Increase your dataset artificially','Use leave-one-out only','k-fold cross-validation','D'),
('data_science','You computed the correlation matrix and two features have correlation of 0.98. What do you do?','Consider removing one to reduce multicollinearity, especially for linear models','Keep both because more features is always better','Replace both with their average','Normalize both features','A'),
('data_science','You run df.describe() and notice the max of a column is 999999 while the 75th percentile is 50. What does this suggest?','The data is normally distributed','There are significant outliers that may skew your model','The column needs to be log-transformed','The data is correct','B'),
('data_science','You plot "age" (0-100) and "income" (0-1000000). Your KNN model performs poorly. Why and what do you do?','KNN does not support large numbers — use log transform','The model needs more neighbors k','The features are irrelevant','KNN is distance-based so income dominates — apply StandardScaler or MinMaxScaler first','C'),
('data_science','You are building a recommendation system and users say recommendations are too similar to what they already bought. What problem is this?','Overfitting','Data leakage','Model underfitting','The filter bubble — too much exploitation and not enough exploration','D'),
('data_science','Your model training takes 6 hours and you want to experiment with hyperparameters. What do you use instead of manual tuning?','GridSearchCV or RandomizedSearchCV or Optuna for automated hyperparameter tuning','Try all combinations manually','Only tune one parameter at a time','Train for fewer epochs','A'),
('data_science','You have a time series dataset and accidentally shuffle data before splitting into train and test. What went wrong?','Shuffling is always fine','Future data leaked into training — time series splits must respect temporal order','The split ratio is wrong','You need more data','B'),
('data_science','You want to apply a custom function to every row of a pandas DataFrame using multiple columns. What is the most readable approach?','Use a for loop','Use df.map(func)','Use df.apply(func, axis=1)','Use numpy vectorize','C'),
('data_science','You build a logistic regression for churn prediction. The business asks "of all churned customers, how many did we catch?" Which metric is this?','Precision','F1-score','Accuracy','Recall','D'),
('data_science','Your Spark job fails with OutOfMemoryError on the driver. What is the most likely cause?','You called .collect() on a large RDD or DataFrame, pulling all data to the driver','Too many workers','The cluster is too small','The data format is wrong','A'),
('data_science','You call df.merge() and end up with far more rows than either original DataFrame. What happened?','The merge created duplicates','You used the wrong merge type','The join key has duplicate values in both DataFrames causing a many-to-many join explosion','One DataFrame is repeated','B'),
('data_science','You want to find customers who purchased in 2024 but NOT in 2023. What SQL approach works?','WHERE year = 2024 AND year != 2023','GROUP BY year HAVING year = 2024','Customers from 2024 EXCEPT customers from 2023, or a LEFT JOIN with IS NULL filter','INNER JOIN between 2024 and 2023 tables','C'),
('data_science','You train a model and pickle it. Six months later predictions are wrong with no code changes. What happened?','The pickle file is corrupted','The Python version changed','The model was not trained properly','Model drift — the real-world data distribution changed since training','D'),
('data_science','You want to reduce a 500-feature dataset to 50 features. Which technique preserves the most variance?','PCA — keeping the top 50 principal components that explain the most variance','Randomly drop 450 features','Drop features with the lowest mean','Use only features with no missing values','A'),
('data_science','Your SQL query on a 50 million row table is very slow. You are filtering by user_id. What do you check first?','Whether the query is written correctly','Whether there is an index on the user_id column','The database server memory','Whether the table is partitioned','B'),
('data_science','You want to detect anomalies in server metrics with no labeled training data. What approach fits?','Train a supervised classifier with normal/anomaly labels','Use linear regression','Use unsupervised methods like Isolation Forest or Autoencoder','Use K-Means with K=2','C'),
('data_science','You use LabelEncoder on your target variable before train/test split. Your colleague says this can bug. Why?','LabelEncoder does not work with strings','LabelEncoder changes the distribution','LabelEncoder should be applied after splitting','If new categories appear in test that were not in training, LabelEncoder will throw an error','D'),
('data_science','You want to standardize your preprocessing and model into a single object that can be fit and applied consistently. What do you use?','A Pipeline','A dictionary of steps','A ColumnTransformer only','A FunctionTransformer','A'),
('data_science','Your A/B test shows variant B has 2% higher conversion. The p-value is 0.08. Can you conclude B is better?','Yes, 2% improvement is meaningful','No, p-value > 0.05 means the result is not statistically significant at the standard threshold','Yes because the sample size is large','No, you need to run the test longer regardless of p-value','B'),
('data_science','You apply pd.get_dummies() to a column with 5 categories and get 5 new columns. What problem can this cause with linear models?','Too many columns slow down training','The model will ignore the new columns','Nothing, this is always correct','Multicollinearity — dummy variable trap. You should drop one category with drop_first=True','C'),
('data_science','You notice your model always predicts the majority class in an imbalanced dataset. What do you try first?','Get more data','Switch to a different model type','Increase the number of trees','Use class_weight="balanced" or SMOTE to handle the imbalance','D'),
('data_science','You have sales data by day and want to compute a 7-day rolling average. What pandas method do you use?','df["sales"].rolling(7).mean()','df["sales"].resample("7D").mean()','df["sales"].cumsum() / 7','df["sales"].ewm(span=7).mean()','A'),
('data_science','You are presenting model results to non-technical stakeholders. Your RMSE is 450. They ask "is that good?". What do you say?','Yes, our model is accurate','RMSE of 450 means our predictions are off by 450 units on average — let me compare this to a baseline','RMSE is a complex metric requiring technical understanding','It depends on the model architecture','B'),
('data_science','You run EXPLAIN on a slow SQL query and see "Seq Scan" on a large table. What does this mean and what should you add?','The query is optimized already','Sequential scan is faster than index scan','The table is too large to index','The database is doing a full table scan — add an index on the filtered column','C'),
